1
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:14,157
Standing way up there…

2
00:01:15,116 --> 00:01:17,494
who would you think of?

3
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:23,041
Jeong…

4
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:21,135
Gosh, it's cold.

5
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:39,255
There.

6
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,985
Okay.

7
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:36,395
I'll call you.
Can you stay somewhere else for a while?

8
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:37,563
Please?

9
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:42,485
Why must I do that?

10
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:45,029
He's at the airport right now.

11
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:47,198
He's coming to see the baby.
What could I do?

12
00:06:50,451 --> 00:06:51,702
Come on, now.

13
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:55,081
Why? Why must I leave my son here
and go somewhere else?

14
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:57,959
He's my son, not yours.

15
00:06:58,042 --> 00:07:00,294
No. He's my son.

16
00:07:00,878 --> 00:07:01,921
I raised him.

17
00:07:02,421 --> 00:07:04,132
Ho-su is my son.

18
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:05,341
Woo-jae.

19
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:09,262
Please, Woo-jae.

20
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:56,517
Hui-ju.

21
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:00,873
Jeong Hui-ju!

22
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:06,045
Hui-ju!

23
00:10:10,484 --> 00:10:15,323
EPISODE 13
SOME TIMES DO NOT DISAPPEAR

24
00:10:16,782 --> 00:10:20,036
TAERIM HOSPITAL

25
00:10:50,024 --> 00:10:53,444
I'm not the lost cause here. It's--

26
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:57,239
Was pestering me not enough?

27
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:59,909
Why do you want her to leave?
Scared of what I'll say?

28
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:35,319
This is the document Mr. Lee got
from Sligo General Hospital.

29
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:53,295
Explain this to me.

30
00:11:58,342 --> 00:12:02,847
Explain why this man
is the guardian on this birth certificate.

31
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:17,153
All the students from Korea were
quite close since we were far from home.

32
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:20,990
Naturally, we helped
each other out when needed.

33
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:31,208
My contractions began
earlier than my due date.

34
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:36,005
And I'm sure you remember
how busy Hyeon-seong was

35
00:12:36,088 --> 00:12:38,549
with setting up
the foundation for Taerim Academy.

36
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,010
I couldn't drive myself.

37
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:44,847
So Mr. Seo drove me to the hospital.

38
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:54,023
He must have signed it
because the hospital staff asked him.

39
00:12:57,401 --> 00:12:58,694
And that's it.

40
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:02,156
I understand this looks suspicious to you,

41
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:03,949
but you have the wrong idea.

42
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:12,625
Did you practice this?
That was very smooth.

43
00:13:14,543 --> 00:13:17,713
Yes, he's your son
because you gave birth to him.

44
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:21,133
But how could I believe you
after seeing this?

45
00:13:29,683 --> 00:13:31,143
Does Hyeon-seong know

46
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:33,646
what you're doing right now?

47
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:35,606
I will tell him once I get the results.

48
00:13:35,689 --> 00:13:38,359
Why didn't you just call him here today?

49
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:43,614
It's been 20 years
since we've been married.

50
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:46,575
It's our marriage, so we'll handle it.

51
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:48,494
This isn't your place to intervene.

52
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:49,620
You…

53
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:58,420
I couldn't care less about your marriage.

54
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:01,715
I'm checking all the boxes to make sure

55
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:05,177
my grandchild is indeed mine
before he inherits my assets.

56
00:14:07,721 --> 00:14:10,683
We'll know for sure tomorrow
if I'm wasting my time or not.

57
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,194
"There was a girl."

58
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:29,702
"Her mind was full of questions
about the world,

59
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:34,623
full of thoughts
about the stars in the night sky,

60
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:41,088
and full of amazement about the ocean."

61
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:47,219
"Whenever she found something new,
she was elated."

62
00:14:49,805 --> 00:14:51,181
"But that was only until…

63
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:56,020
she saw the empty chair
her grandpa used to sit in."

64
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:02,067
What? Are you crying?

65
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:05,112
Why?

66
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:07,531
Well, it's sad.

67
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,575
Which part?

68
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:13,495
You wouldn't know even if I told you.

69
00:15:13,579 --> 00:15:14,997
I'll know if you tell me.

70
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:20,377
Sadness is something you feel.
It can't be understood through words.

71
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:26,383
Then I think I feel it too.

72
00:15:27,259 --> 00:15:31,472
-What?
-Because I don't feel good either.

73
00:15:36,518 --> 00:15:37,728
I'm sorry, Ho-su.

74
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:40,105
I'm really sorry.

75
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:41,607
It's okay.

76
00:15:42,483 --> 00:15:45,861
Ma'am, you don't have to
apologize for being sad.

77
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:58,624
"The scared girl decided to put her heart
in a bottle just for a little while."

78
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:02,836
Why did she put her heart in a bottle?

79
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:04,088
Well…

80
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:08,467
Maybe keeping her heart
was too painful for her.

81
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:10,219
Why was it painful?

82
00:16:11,553 --> 00:16:14,014
It happens when you lose
something precious to you.

83
00:16:14,598 --> 00:16:16,725
What does "precious" mean?

84
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:19,144
Something is precious
when there's only one of that.

85
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:21,230
The only one in the world.

86
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,406
But you have to be careful.

87
00:16:30,489 --> 00:16:32,741
If you put your heart
in the bottle for too long,

88
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:34,618
you'll forget other feelings too.

89
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:00,144
Ho-su…

90
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:02,563
Ho-su…

91
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,531
I told you to stay away.

92
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,617
I'm not here to see Hui-ju.

93
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:20,664
And I made myself very clear as well.
I never forgave her.

94
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:23,208
-Ms. Gu.
-You said you love her.

95
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:26,795
You couldn't have forgiven her that easily
if you truly loved her.

96
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:33,177
Or it's, "Since I forgave you,

97
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:35,804
I'm a better person than you."

98
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:38,640
"I'm the most ethical man."

99
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:41,727
Is that your way of comforting yourself?

100
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:48,400
Seeing you try
to keep your dignity to the end

101
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:51,195
makes you look pathetic, not respectable.

102
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:55,616
It's natural to break down
and get jealous when you've been betrayed.

103
00:17:55,699 --> 00:17:58,285
But you don't want
to show people that you are weak?

104
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,373
How about you?
You think you're doing well?

105
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:15,803
You say you're getting revenge,
but you seem more distressed.

106
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:19,264
No matter how distressed I am,
it is easier than being forgiving.

107
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:23,143
You two can try whatever you want,
but I'm not going to leave my wife.

108
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:25,062
And my wife feels the same too.

109
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:27,981
So let me tell you this one last time.

110
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:32,653
You should stop here.
I mean this. I really do.

111
00:18:34,988 --> 00:18:37,282
I don't want to hurt you.

112
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:50,337
Ho-su.

113
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:57,719
I hope you don't blame me.

114
00:18:59,054 --> 00:19:01,515
I'm not as experienced as you.

115
00:19:02,349 --> 00:19:04,685
So I can't say no to our mother-in-law.

116
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:15,863
Mom, I can't breathe.

117
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:18,699
Right. I'm sorry.

118
00:19:21,368 --> 00:19:24,872
You know how much I love you, right?

119
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:30,460
You know how precious
you are to me. Right?

120
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:32,629
Yes, I know.

121
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:35,507
Because you only have one Ho-su.

122
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:38,135
The one and only in the world.

123
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:46,727
What are you doing here, honey?

124
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:57,154
It's all right, Hui-ju.

125
00:20:07,539 --> 00:20:09,166
Go home with Ho-su.

126
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:11,460
Don't worry.

127
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:13,128
Why? What are you going to do?

128
00:20:13,712 --> 00:20:16,173
Whatever it is,
there's nothing to gain from avoiding it.

129
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:19,134
Don't go. Your mother--

130
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:22,888
What is it? Are there more things
we should be worried about?

131
00:20:27,517 --> 00:20:28,685
No.

132
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:32,189
Then trust me.
I'm your husband and Ho-su's father.

133
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:58,298
How did you find out?

134
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:00,300
Did she call you already?

135
00:21:01,843 --> 00:21:02,886
What's this?

136
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:08,475
What do you think you're doing?

137
00:21:08,558 --> 00:21:10,102
Ho-su is my son.

138
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:14,940
I'm sure you want to believe that,
so let's check to make sure.

139
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:19,111
We don't need this test.

140
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:24,241
Did you already get the test done?

141
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:29,121
Do you think
I let you marry her for your sake?

142
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:33,750
When you told me
she was pregnant and the only one for you,

143
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:35,294
I had already given up on you.

144
00:21:36,253 --> 00:21:37,963
I let you two get married

145
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:41,383
so that I could raise an heir
to take your place since you were useless.

146
00:21:41,883 --> 00:21:43,927
I put up with you
because I needed a grandson!

147
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,012
Mom, please!

148
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:47,347
You must've gotten the test for a reason.

149
00:21:52,853 --> 00:21:55,063
Your reactions prove my suspicion right.

150
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:57,816
I can tell you're hiding something nasty.

151
00:21:58,692 --> 00:22:00,944
I don't care what the results say.
Divorce her!

152
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:06,700
I'm turning 50 soon.

153
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:11,580
I don't think I can start over at my age.

154
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:13,915
If she leaves, I leave too.

155
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:16,251
-Hey!
-You did the same thing!

156
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:19,338
Even until his very last breath,

157
00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:23,675
-you didn't let go of Father.
-I hated what he did.

158
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:27,262
I helped him build everything he had.

159
00:22:27,929 --> 00:22:31,433
That self-pitying man prided himself
on his smarts and was never grateful.

160
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:34,686
Lowlifes always act like that.

161
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,689
They delude themselves
into thinking they earned it.

162
00:22:39,149 --> 00:22:40,525
You think she's any different?

163
00:22:41,818 --> 00:22:43,737
She's different. I know her.

164
00:22:43,820 --> 00:22:45,614
Don't be so sure.

165
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:47,741
I thought I knew your father too.

166
00:22:50,786 --> 00:22:52,204
But I was wrong.

167
00:22:53,497 --> 00:22:56,666
I lived with him for 30 years,
but I still didn't know who he was.

168
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:58,251
I knew nothing about him!

169
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:03,548
Because of him,
he tarnished my entire life!

170
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:08,845
Your father made me feel insignificant!

171
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:15,644
Are you sure…

172
00:23:18,188 --> 00:23:20,023
you won't end up like me?

173
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:58,937
"The scared girl decided to put her heart
in a bottle just for a little while…

174
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:01,898
because her heart might get hurt."

175
00:24:03,608 --> 00:24:05,819
"When she did, her heart stopped hurting."

176
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:10,323
"But her thoughts about the stars

177
00:24:10,407 --> 00:24:13,326
and her interest
in the ocean disappeared."

178
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:15,871
"Soon enough,

179
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:19,624
the girl lost her love and curiosity

180
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:21,960
for the world."

181
00:25:13,887 --> 00:25:17,224
Then trust me.
I'm your husband and Ho-su's father.

182
00:25:28,652 --> 00:25:33,031
Be careful of the overhead bins
as the contents may fall out.

183
00:26:05,814 --> 00:26:08,942
I don't think there's any need
to try to remember what's already past.

184
00:26:09,901 --> 00:26:12,487
If you don't remember it,
then it's never happened.

185
00:26:30,380 --> 00:26:31,548
Mr. Lee.

186
00:26:35,635 --> 00:26:37,429
I'll stay here and talk.

187
00:26:40,223 --> 00:26:43,393
A line is there for a reason.
Don't cross the line.

188
00:26:46,104 --> 00:26:47,063
I don't follow.

189
00:26:47,147 --> 00:26:49,607
Don't think
I haven't said anything about you

190
00:26:51,026 --> 00:26:52,944
and my sister because I don't know.

191
00:26:55,864 --> 00:26:58,033
She and I might not be that close,

192
00:26:58,908 --> 00:27:02,162
but she'll choose me over you
because if your marriage goes south,

193
00:27:02,245 --> 00:27:04,289
you will practically be a stranger to her.

194
00:27:05,290 --> 00:27:08,501
If you're upset about
what happened to Hui-ju, your mother--

195
00:27:08,585 --> 00:27:10,295
I know. I do.

196
00:27:13,548 --> 00:27:15,592
But that's my business.

197
00:27:16,968 --> 00:27:18,887
So stop meddling in my affairs.

198
00:27:21,598 --> 00:27:22,599
You can go.

199
00:27:40,241 --> 00:27:43,286
Instead of arranging the pieces
at eye level like before,

200
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:47,374
what do you think about
placing it slightly lower?

201
00:27:47,457 --> 00:27:50,251
I see. That's an original approach.

202
00:27:50,877 --> 00:27:52,754
It's worth trying it out.

203
00:27:52,837 --> 00:27:57,550
And I want ample space between the pieces

204
00:27:57,634 --> 00:28:02,055
for the visitors to have more time
to appreciate the pieces.

205
00:28:02,806 --> 00:28:04,516
To get a better understanding…

206
00:28:14,150 --> 00:28:15,402
Do you have the results?

207
00:28:16,403 --> 00:28:19,072
PROBABILITY OF PATERNITY: 99.999%
AN HYEON-SEONG, FATHER

208
00:28:19,155 --> 00:28:20,907
AN HO-SU, SON

209
00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:28,873
Don't think this makes everything go away.

210
00:28:29,624 --> 00:28:31,376
I saw how you reacted yesterday.

211
00:28:33,002 --> 00:28:35,255
There must be some history
between you and him.

212
00:28:37,298 --> 00:28:38,800
How could anyone

213
00:28:38,883 --> 00:28:41,719
not get flustered
after being accused like that?

214
00:28:42,637 --> 00:28:46,975
It seemed Hyeon-seong had already known,
but he just wouldn't talk about it.

215
00:28:52,105 --> 00:28:56,443
I wonder what on earth you did
to have him wrapped around your finger.

216
00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:01,656
I won't let this go
just because you two seem okay with it.

217
00:29:03,241 --> 00:29:04,117
Now get out.

218
00:29:08,705 --> 00:29:10,999
DNA PATERNITY TEST RESULTS

219
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:40,445
I didn't have time for lunch.
So I'm having this instead.

220
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:44,324
You and Jeong-hwan
will stay here this summer.

221
00:29:44,407 --> 00:29:46,701
Summer is a critical time for Jeong-hwan.

222
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:49,204
A three-week summer program
will increase his options.

223
00:29:49,287 --> 00:29:52,499
It's just college.
Like your mother said, it's not important.

224
00:29:53,082 --> 00:29:56,336
He takes after you and me.
There's no doubt that he's a smart kid.

225
00:29:56,836 --> 00:29:59,255
Studying is not
what Jeong-hwan needs right now.

226
00:30:00,507 --> 00:30:02,008
It's your mother's attention.

227
00:30:02,592 --> 00:30:05,929
But still, he has an interest
he wants to pursue. Why don't we--

228
00:30:06,012 --> 00:30:07,972
Why study how dolphins communicate?

229
00:30:08,056 --> 00:30:10,183
How will that help him
inherit the foundation?

230
00:30:12,268 --> 00:30:16,272
You know that my mother loves sons.

231
00:30:18,650 --> 00:30:21,236
She has Hyeon-seong.
She wouldn't consider me.

232
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:24,697
I'll never see eye to eye with her.

233
00:30:29,118 --> 00:30:32,247
The higher hopes she has for him,
the more betrayed she'll feel.

234
00:30:33,081 --> 00:30:34,916
This is the time to win her over.

235
00:30:35,625 --> 00:30:38,169
We may have to do
whatever she tells us to do,

236
00:30:38,253 --> 00:30:41,631
but shouldn't we, as his parents,
help our son hold the reins?

237
00:30:45,343 --> 00:30:47,262
Have Jeong-hwan
attend med school in Korea.

238
00:30:48,346 --> 00:30:50,348
He has a chance to be a doctor

239
00:30:50,431 --> 00:30:53,726
and the head of a hospital
just like you wanted.

240
00:30:55,478 --> 00:30:57,897
How much longer
will you lose out to your brother?

241
00:30:58,439 --> 00:31:00,900
Who do you think is running this hospital?

242
00:31:07,448 --> 00:31:09,868
Mr. Seo moved up
his return flight to Korea.

243
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:11,703
He'll be arriving today.

244
00:31:12,829 --> 00:31:14,539
Right before leaving Ireland,

245
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:17,292
he stopped by Sligo General Hospital.

246
00:31:26,009 --> 00:31:27,010
There's your mom.

247
00:31:27,093 --> 00:31:29,137
-Mom!
-Ho-su.

248
00:31:29,637 --> 00:31:30,930
This is for you, Mom.

249
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:36,603
This is for me? I wonder what it is.

250
00:31:37,854 --> 00:31:39,147
Is this a vase?

251
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:42,734
You can put your heart
in the bottle when it hurts, okay?

252
00:31:45,445 --> 00:31:47,739
How did you come up
with such a sweet thought?

253
00:31:48,239 --> 00:31:49,407
