00:52:50,709 --> 00:52:53,253
There's no way
she fell for someone weak like you.

513
00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:55,130
It was my mistake for coming here.

514
00:52:57,632 --> 00:53:00,051
I was never interested in Hui-ju at first.

515
00:53:00,886 --> 00:53:03,346
But Hae-won wouldn't stop
talking about her.

516
00:53:04,973 --> 00:53:08,018
So it piqued my curiosity.
That's how it started.

517
00:53:08,768 --> 00:53:12,355
But it turned out she was nothing
more than just a lonely married woman.

518
00:53:13,648 --> 00:53:14,524
She was easy.

519
00:53:15,150 --> 00:53:17,944
She easily fell for me
after I made some advances.

520
00:53:18,987 --> 00:53:20,322
There was no fun in it.

521
00:53:24,618 --> 00:53:26,995
Were you always such a pathetic loser?

522
00:53:27,078 --> 00:53:30,624
Yes. She easily fell for a loser like me.

523
00:53:31,666 --> 00:53:33,710
You think
she'll be faithful to you forever?

524
00:53:51,019 --> 00:53:53,438
Since you're here,
why don't you pay for my drink?

525
00:53:54,439 --> 00:53:59,611
I've been enjoying my stay in Ireland
thanks to the money you've been sending.

526
00:56:01,357 --> 00:56:02,442
This isn't…

527
00:56:30,220 --> 00:56:34,808
HUI-JU

528
00:56:42,607 --> 00:56:43,525
Hey.

529
00:56:44,275 --> 00:56:46,611
I've been calling you. Where are you?

530
00:56:49,030 --> 00:56:50,073
I had…

531
00:56:52,325 --> 00:56:53,576
some work left to do.

532
00:56:54,494 --> 00:56:56,996
I was worried.
You disappeared after we checked in.

533
00:56:59,874 --> 00:57:00,917
Sorry.

534
00:57:04,712 --> 00:57:06,881
I'll be there soon.

535
00:57:17,100 --> 00:57:20,937
It is my understanding that
my lawyer gave you the incident report.

536
00:57:23,481 --> 00:57:25,608
Yes, I got it.

537
00:57:26,568 --> 00:57:28,736
But it's written in so much detail

538
00:57:29,821 --> 00:57:32,657
that I have the feeling
the most important part was buried.

539
00:57:35,493 --> 00:57:36,619
Buried?

540
00:57:38,705 --> 00:57:39,789
Nonsense.

541
00:57:40,874 --> 00:57:43,084
What would we need to bury
about your incident?

542
00:57:49,007 --> 00:57:50,216
Let's set a date.

543
00:57:51,384 --> 00:57:54,220
I'm sure my wife would
like to hear about your trip to Ireland.

544
00:57:54,304 --> 00:57:57,098
Why don't the three of us meet up soon?

545
00:57:57,182 --> 00:57:59,017
Actually, I already called her today.

546
00:58:00,435 --> 00:58:01,853
I'll see you next time.

547
00:58:15,617 --> 00:58:18,244
CHAIRMAN'S OFFICE

548
00:58:20,246 --> 00:58:21,664
What are you doing here?

549
00:58:22,582 --> 00:58:24,417
I needed to ask your dad something.

550
00:58:25,168 --> 00:58:26,961
Ask what? What did you ask him?

551
00:58:27,045 --> 00:58:28,421
Do you read books?

552
00:58:29,464 --> 00:58:31,633
The flower you asked me
about before. The heath.

553
00:58:31,716 --> 00:58:35,178
That flower comes up a lot
in a novel called Wuthering Heights.

554
00:58:35,261 --> 00:58:36,471
Give it a read.

555
00:58:37,263 --> 00:58:39,557
What? What is that book about?

556
00:58:55,532 --> 00:58:58,451
Your call could not be connected.
After the tone…

557
00:59:00,787 --> 00:59:02,080
FAVORITES
WOO-JAE

558
00:59:02,163 --> 00:59:04,874
WOO-JAE'S LOCATION CANNOT BE FOUND

559
00:59:09,879 --> 00:59:11,548
DIRECTOR AN HYEON-SEONG

560
00:59:13,258 --> 00:59:14,217
Hello.

561
00:59:14,968 --> 00:59:16,761
Let's try that again.

562
00:59:16,844 --> 00:59:18,054
-Okay.
-Okay.

563
00:59:20,765 --> 00:59:24,227
Do you want us to die because
you are afraid of future criticism?

564
00:59:24,310 --> 00:59:28,356
What you're talking about right now
requires billions…

565
00:59:28,439 --> 00:59:32,151
I did hear that you're a fan of theatre
and even fund them

566
00:59:32,235 --> 00:59:34,070
when I was working at the school.

567
00:59:34,571 --> 00:59:36,364
I guess you really love them.

568
00:59:39,033 --> 00:59:40,910
We should suspend the contract.

569
00:59:41,578 --> 00:59:42,912
The gallery is just a start.

570
00:59:43,413 --> 00:59:45,915
Once I expand the gallery
into an art center…

571
00:59:47,750 --> 00:59:49,627
I plan to set up a theater there too.

572
00:59:50,211 --> 00:59:51,546
Thanks to my wife,

573
00:59:53,298 --> 00:59:56,175
I have a chance
to fulfill my dream at my age.

574
00:59:57,010 --> 00:59:58,219
Any other questions?

575
01:00:00,888 --> 01:00:05,143
I remember
when you took the entire faculty

576
01:00:06,603 --> 01:00:07,729
to the opera.

577
01:00:11,566 --> 01:00:12,984
What was it called?

578
01:00:15,612 --> 01:00:17,280
It was about a clown

579
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:20,283
who had to entertain the audience
while his wife had an affair.

580
01:00:22,577 --> 01:00:24,329
It was your story.

581
01:00:25,913 --> 01:00:27,332
I saw that day

582
01:00:28,291 --> 01:00:30,293
how much pain you were in.

583
01:00:35,423 --> 01:00:37,550
If your limbs were broken or something,

584
01:00:38,343 --> 01:00:41,846
people would have tried
to understand your pain even for a moment.

585
01:00:43,181 --> 01:00:48,144
It's very hard to be understood
about pain no one else can see.

586
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:54,942
Did Mr. Seo…

587
01:00:58,404 --> 01:01:00,323
get his memories back?

588
01:01:04,369 --> 01:01:06,079
You must've met him.

589
01:01:07,622 --> 01:01:09,874
I wanted him to get his memories back.

590
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:13,503
But his reaction is totally unexpected.

591
01:01:17,632 --> 01:01:21,636
It must be even more flustering
for those who have something to hide.

592
01:01:30,520 --> 01:01:32,313
You're really going to sell it?

593
01:01:32,397 --> 01:01:33,356
Yes.

594
01:01:34,148 --> 01:01:36,901
I told you.
An ecological park will be built here.

595
01:01:36,984 --> 01:01:40,238
They wanted to rid of the cause
of pollution and improve water quality.

596
01:01:40,321 --> 01:01:44,367
So they are going to demolish
everything in this area

597
01:01:44,450 --> 01:01:46,285
including fishing spots and docks.

598
01:01:46,369 --> 01:01:49,914
But you know what I did?
I upped the compensation money.

599
01:01:56,504 --> 01:01:58,381
-Who is it?
-My mom.

600
01:01:59,465 --> 01:02:01,092
It must be her superpower.

601
01:02:02,635 --> 01:02:05,430
She always calls me
when I'm going through a hard time.

602
01:02:05,513 --> 01:02:07,056
What is it this time?

603
01:02:07,140 --> 01:02:09,851
Exactly. What does she want this time?

604
01:02:10,518 --> 01:02:11,978
I'm not even curious.

605
01:02:13,604 --> 01:02:17,024
I'm just worried if I don't answer,
she might call my husband,

606
01:02:17,900 --> 01:02:19,819
and that my mother-in-law

607
01:02:20,486 --> 01:02:21,654
might find out.

608
01:02:25,032 --> 01:02:27,410
I think that must've been why.

609
01:02:27,493 --> 01:02:29,245
What? What do you mean?

610
01:02:30,371 --> 01:02:34,208
With Woo-jae, I didn't have
a mother-in-law I had to impress.

611
01:02:34,876 --> 01:02:38,671
And I didn't have to
be this good wife or mother.

612
01:02:40,089 --> 01:02:44,010
When I was with him, I could be myself,
forget about everything else,

613
01:02:44,719 --> 01:02:46,763
and just do what I wanted to do.

614
01:03:09,243 --> 01:03:11,120
I think I've given you enough time.

615
01:03:12,497 --> 01:03:13,706
So tell me.

616
01:03:18,252 --> 01:03:19,378
Let's break up.

617
01:03:21,672 --> 01:03:23,508
I should have done it a long time ago.

618
01:03:24,759 --> 01:03:25,885
But I was a coward.

619
01:03:27,011 --> 01:03:27,929
I'm sorry.

620
01:03:29,430 --> 01:03:30,306
You're sorry?

621
01:03:31,349 --> 01:03:32,433
Yes.

622
01:03:34,519 --> 01:03:38,439
So your memories really came back.
You haven't changed at all.

623
01:03:39,273 --> 01:03:41,526
You're not sorry at all.

624
01:03:41,609 --> 01:03:43,444
You already forgave yourself.

625
01:03:44,153 --> 01:03:45,988
That's why you're shamelessly telling me

626
01:03:46,531 --> 01:03:48,950
you want to break up
before apologizing to me.

627
01:03:49,033 --> 01:03:50,159
Break up with me.

628
01:03:50,952 --> 01:03:53,996
If you don't, I'll abandon you again.

629
01:03:54,747 --> 01:03:57,041
Again?

630
01:03:57,708 --> 01:04:01,462
What? Do you think you have a shot
with Hui-ju if you break up with me?

631
01:04:01,546 --> 01:04:02,672
I'll make it so.

632
01:04:03,756 --> 01:04:05,675
I'll be the man she deserves

633
01:04:06,342 --> 01:04:07,969
and make her come back to me.

634
01:04:08,052 --> 01:04:11,264
You're sick, Woo-jae. You're an addict.

635
01:04:11,889 --> 01:04:14,058
Alcohol and drugs
aren't the only addictions.

636
01:04:14,141 --> 01:04:15,601
You get addicted to people too.

637
01:04:15,685 --> 01:04:18,771
You know that you're
hurting others and ruining your life,

638
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:21,482
but you can't let go or escape.

639
01:04:22,775 --> 01:04:24,068
That's an addiction.

640
01:04:24,652 --> 01:04:25,653
Are you any different?

641
01:04:27,071 --> 01:04:30,324
Can't you see how messed up you've become?

642
01:04:34,161 --> 01:04:35,121
Right.

643
01:04:36,289 --> 01:04:38,457
I became addicted
to Hui-ju along with you.

644
01:04:39,709 --> 01:04:43,713
That's why you and I can
never escape each other.

645
01:04:55,683 --> 01:04:57,143
Who is it? Why don't you answer?

646
01:04:57,226 --> 01:05:00,187
It's my mom.
She's been calling me all day.

647
01:05:00,271 --> 01:05:01,772
Her restaurant opens this week.

648
01:05:02,440 --> 01:05:03,691
Is it about the restaurant?

649
01:05:03,774 --> 01:05:06,277
No, it's nothing.
I already talked to her once earlier.

650
01:05:06,360 --> 01:05:09,280
-You should still answer it.
-Don't.

651
01:05:10,364 --> 01:05:13,743
She must be feeling what I felt waiting
for her to call when she left home.

652
01:05:26,964 --> 01:05:29,425
SEO WOO-JAE

653
01:05:41,687 --> 01:05:43,397
Answer it.

654
01:05:52,657 --> 01:05:57,620
SEO WOO-JAE:
LET'S MEET. PICK UP THE PHONE.

655
01:05:57,703 --> 01:05:59,705
INCOMING CALL
SEO WOO-JAE

656
01:06:09,423 --> 01:06:11,008
DELETE MESSAGES

657
01:06:11,092 --> 01:06:13,135
SELECT MESSAGES

658
01:06:13,219 --> 01:06:14,387
MESSAGES

659
01:06:17,348 --> 01:06:18,432
CALLS

660
01:06:18,516 --> 01:06:23,229
SELECTED
SEO WOO-JAE

661
01:06:35,241 --> 01:06:37,493
Don't. Don't leave.

662
01:06:38,786 --> 01:06:40,121
I told you.

663
01:06:40,204 --> 01:06:42,331
I forgive you. Don't leave me.

664
01:06:42,415 --> 01:06:45,334
I…

665
01:06:46,210 --> 01:06:48,254
I told you.

666
01:06:48,754 --> 01:06:52,133
I told you I love you.

667
01:07:19,577 --> 01:07:20,870
That's so sudden.

668
01:07:21,620 --> 01:07:23,414
Actually, it's not so sudden.

669
01:07:24,206 --> 01:07:28,419
Mr. Woo is quite old.
His illness must have worsened.

670
01:07:29,503 --> 01:07:32,048
And I think he always knew how bad it was.

671
01:07:32,131 --> 01:07:34,550
He probably thought
this would be his last project,

672
01:07:34,633 --> 01:07:36,969
so he was especially
attached to this project.

673
01:07:37,053 --> 01:07:40,639
Then we should make it special for him.

674
01:07:41,974 --> 01:07:44,351
So I was wondering if it would be okay

675
01:07:44,435 --> 01:07:48,230
to display his old pieces
at this exhibition.

676
01:07:49,565 --> 01:07:51,901
They're a part
of Korean architectural history.

677
01:07:51,984 --> 01:07:53,944
Designs are also artwork.

678
01:07:54,028 --> 01:07:56,072
The models are amazing too.

679
01:07:56,864 --> 01:07:59,617
Instead of simply exhibiting his work,

680
01:07:59,700 --> 01:08:02,495
can we do something special with them?

681
01:08:03,579 --> 01:08:06,290
I will have to see them
in person to get inspired.

682
01:08:06,373 --> 01:08:10,336
Mr. Woo already donated them to us,
so I already brought them here.

683
01:08:13,339 --> 01:08:16,217
Goodness. I told them to organize these.

684
01:08:18,302 --> 01:08:20,054
-Excuse me for a moment.
-Okay.

685
01:08:20,137 --> 01:08:24,517
Yes. Actually, I was going to call you.

686
01:08:24,600 --> 01:08:26,143
Thank you for calling me first.

687
01:08:29,814 --> 01:08:30,898
ARCHITECT WOO JEONG-HYO

688
01:08:48,999 --> 01:08:50,042
Don't avoid me.

689
01:08:50,751 --> 01:08:52,336
I don't care if you're married.

690
01:08:53,796 --> 01:08:56,757
I never cared about that then,
and I still don't.

691
01:08:58,717 --> 01:09:00,052
You're good at it.

692
01:09:01,595 --> 01:09:03,472
You can have a marriage with him

693
01:09:04,807 --> 01:09:06,183
and be in love with me.

694
01:09:12,398 --> 01:09:13,399
You…

695
01:09:19,613 --> 01:09:20,656
Ms. Jeong?

696
01:09:26,662 --> 01:09:29,748
Goodness, Mr. Seo. You came really early.

697
01:09:29,832 --> 01:09:31,417
I wanted to see the artwork beforehand.

698
01:09:33,627 --> 01:09:35,254
Where's Ms. Jeong?

699
01:09:35,337 --> 01:09:37,590
You didn't see her? She was just here.

700
01:09:40,134 --> 01:09:41,427
Ms. Jeong?

701
01:10:00,446 --> 01:10:03,032
Answer me. You didn't give me your answer.

702
01:10:04,992 --> 01:10:06,493
What answer?

703
01:10:07,077 --> 01:10:08,495
Go out with me.

704
01:10:08,579 --> 01:10:09,538
Why would I?

705
01:10:10,956 --> 01:10:11,999
Have you gone mad?

706
01:10:14,501 --> 01:10:16,462
Then why did you see me back then?

707
01:10:18,172 --> 01:10:19,089
Out of loneliness?

708
01:10:21,675 --> 01:10:23,928
Out of boredom? For fun?

709
01:10:25,846 --> 01:10:28,557
Yes! And I don't want this now.

710
01:10:32,603 --> 01:10:35,481
What brings you here?
Why didn't you call me you were coming?

711
01:10:37,233 --> 01:10:39,193
I thought you wouldn't answer it.

712
01:10:39,276 --> 01:10:42,696
-What are you talking--
-Let's go. We'll talk on the way.

713
01:10:43,447 --> 01:10:46,283
I'll call you again, Ms. Jeong.

714
01:10:47,993 --> 01:10:49,078
Sure.

715
01:11:09,640 --> 01:11:13,560
SEATS AVAILABLE UPSTAIRS
OPEN 24 HOURS

716
01:11:23,654 --> 01:11:25,906
My son-in-law is the chairman of a school.

717
01:11:25,990 --> 01:11:27,324
-Gosh.
-The chairman.

718
01:11:27,408 --> 01:11:28,701
-Gosh.
-You must be so happy.

719
01:11:29,368 --> 01:11:30,828
-Please enjoy.
-Sure.

720
01:11:30,911 --> 01:11:33,080
-Come often. She's my mother-in-law.
-Thank you.

721
01:11:34,707 --> 01:11:37,334
It's only once or twice a year. I'm fine.

722
01:11:37,960 --> 01:11:40,921
I called her because
I was concerned. I did.

723
01:11:41,755 --> 01:11:44,008
She doesn't appreciate your efforts.

724
01:11:44,883 --> 01:11:46,343
Don't be nice to my mom.

725
01:11:49,430 --> 01:11:51,098
But you're good to my mom.

726
01:11:51,807 --> 01:11:53,392
That's different.

727
01:11:54,059 --> 01:11:55,227
How is it different?

728
01:12:02,735 --> 01:12:03,819
Earlier today,

729
01:12:04,945 --> 01:12:07,990
we had a last-minute meeting

730
01:12:08,073 --> 01:12:11,201
because the architect on our project
had suddenly fallen ill.

731
01:12:11,827 --> 01:12:13,203
Don't get the wrong idea.

732
01:12:15,080 --> 01:12:16,332
I won't.

733
01:12:18,334 --> 01:12:22,129
The look on your face told me
that you were uncomfortable around him.

734
01:12:24,798 --> 01:12:27,509
Your mother put
a lot of effort into this restaurant.

735
01:12:27,593 --> 01:12:31,305
She handpicked all the dishes on the menu.
And she's taking care of everything.

736
01:12:32,973 --> 01:12:34,266
She's working really hard.

737
01:12:34,767 --> 01:12:37,019
It's nice to support her when she is.

738
01:12:39,021 --> 01:12:40,647
I hope it works out.

739
01:12:42,149 --> 01:12:43,901
This act of kindness isn't for her.

740
01:12:47,196 --> 01:12:50,616
Can you please play with me?

741
01:12:50,699 --> 01:12:52,034
How should I play with you?

742
01:12:52,785 --> 01:12:54,953
Ho-su, it's time to go to bed now.

743
01:12:56,121 --> 01:12:57,414
You have a lot of work. Go.

744
01:12:57,498 --> 01:12:59,541
-I'll tuck him in.
-Thank you.

745
01:12:59,625 --> 01:13:02,211
What do you say? Should I tuck you in?

746
01:13:05,047 --> 01:13:06,215
He is…

747
01:13:07,758 --> 01:13:08,926
showing me

748
01:13:09,968 --> 01:13:13,555
my weaknesses one by one.

749
01:13:20,479 --> 01:13:22,231
I don't care if you're married.

750
01:13:22,314 --> 01:13:25,025
I never cared about that then,
and I still don't.

751
01:13:25,734 --> 01:13:26,985
You're good at it.

752
01:13:28,612 --> 01:13:30,531
You can have a marriage with him

753
01:13:31,865 --> 01:13:33,409
and be in love with me.

754
01:13:46,964 --> 01:13:53,637
SEO WOO-JAE

755
01:14:08,694 --> 01:14:11,405
Did you call me here,
so I can watch you throw a fit?

756
01:14:13,407 --> 01:14:15,325
I don't know what people want.

757
01:14:19,413 --> 01:14:21,457
I must do it even if I have to fake it.

758
01:14:23,417 --> 01:14:24,543
But this is…

759
01:14:31,425 --> 01:14:32,509
Don't go.

760
01:14:33,427 --> 01:14:34,636
I'm trying.

761
01:14:35,262 --> 01:14:36,889
Can't you just put up with me…

762
01:14:39,057 --> 01:14:40,350
even if I throw a fit?

763
01:14:44,396 --> 01:14:47,107
Mr. Seo. Listen carefully.

764
01:14:47,983 --> 01:14:50,652
I came here to give you my answer
because I didn't want

765
01:14:50,736 --> 01:14:52,779
the lack of my answer to mislead you.

766
01:14:54,573 --> 01:14:57,159
Once this project is over,

767
01:14:57,242 --> 01:14:59,536
you and I are colleagues
who will never meet again.

768
01:15:00,787 --> 01:15:01,872
That's all.

769
01:15:07,085 --> 01:15:08,253
You have

770
01:15:09,671 --> 01:15:11,006
my answer now. All right?

771
01:15:29,107 --> 01:15:30,817
This was a present from you.

772
01:15:32,611 --> 01:15:34,655
You took everything, but not this.

773
01:15:39,993 --> 01:15:43,413
You shouldn't have left without giving me
a chance to make it work.

774
01:16:04,643 --> 01:16:06,228
I'll do better this time.

775
01:16:09,022 --> 01:16:10,023
Give me a chance.

776
01:16:22,202 --> 01:16:23,954
Do you remember what you told me?

777
01:16:26,248 --> 01:16:27,457
You said

778
01:16:28,834 --> 01:16:32,212
a broken marriage wasn't something
you could piece back together.

779
01:16:36,967 --> 01:16:38,051
Come back

780
01:16:39,094 --> 01:16:40,137
to me.

781
01:16:43,974 --> 01:16:45,684
Love me like you did back then.

782
01:16:47,102 --> 01:16:48,770
You can throw me away again.

783
01:16:49,730 --> 01:16:51,398
That's my burden to bear.

784
01:16:52,316 --> 01:16:54,526
I'll endure the broken heart.

785
01:16:58,655 --> 01:17:00,157
So just love me now.

786
01:17:19,968 --> 01:17:22,137
I won't let you run off this time.

787
01:17:23,472 --> 01:17:25,015
I'm going to get back everything

788
01:17:26,683 --> 01:17:27,851
that I lost.

789
01:18:12,938 --> 01:18:15,023
When will you stop clinging to the past?

790
01:18:15,107 --> 01:18:16,566
Don't long for it.

791
01:18:18,276 --> 01:18:20,028
Who are you to judge my feelings?

792
01:18:20,112 --> 01:18:22,072
I haven't even started yet.

793
01:18:22,155 --> 01:18:25,742
Take good care of her.
She seems to be struggling lately.

794
01:18:25,826 --> 01:18:27,035
I'm not her husband anymore.

795
01:18:28,787 --> 01:18:30,080
So what makes you so different?

796
01:18:30,163 --> 01:18:32,124
You enjoyed it while knowing his feelings.

797
01:18:32,207 --> 01:18:33,709
You're just a cheater.

798
01:18:33,792 --> 01:18:35,377
Hui-ju doesn't want you back.

799
01:18:35,460 --> 01:18:38,213
What have you done to him?

800
01:18:38,296 --> 01:18:39,798
He's a man, after all.

801
01:18:41,049 --> 01:18:42,092
Then choose.

802
01:18:42,175 --> 01:18:45,470
Is it your family or that bastard?

803
01:18:45,554 --> 01:18:46,430
Let me go!

804
01:18:47,305 --> 01:18:49,307
I will kill anyone

805
01:18:51,309 --> 01:18:52,477
who dares to harm you.

806
01:18:55,564 --> 01:19:00,569
